task_description: Facing the building to your North (approx. 11°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: To estimate the building's height, I need to view its full vertical structure; rotating the camera upward will reveal the roofline for accurate measurement.
The current upward pitch of 30° may not fully capture the building's roof; increasing pitch further will reveal the top structure for accurate height estimation.
The building's roof is still not fully visible at 30° pitch; further upward rotation is required to capture the top structure for accurate height estimation.
The building's roof remains partially obscured; increasing pitch to 60° should fully reveal the top structure for accurate height calculation using trigonometric principles.
The building's roof remains partially visible; increasing pitch to 60° should fully capture the vertical structure for height calculation using trigonometric principles with estimated distance.

After multiple upward rotations, the building's roof remains obscured; moving backward to a greater distance will provide a wider field of view to capture the full vertical structure for accurate height estimation.
